SSH : SECURE SHELL

    CHECK INSTALLED : file /etc/ssh/sshd_config

    INSTALL : sudo apt install openssh-client openssh-server

    START SERVICE : sudo systemctl start ssh
    
    CONNECT : ssh UserName@IP_Address

    WITHOUT PASSWORD : 

        GENERATE KEY : ssh-keygen

        LIST FILES : ls .ssh

        COPY PUBLIC KEY : ssh-copy-id UserName@IP_Address


GRAPHICAL TOOLS : 

    PUTTY TERMINAL : 
    WINSCP :


SCP : SECURE COPY PROTOCOL

    SEND COPIED FILES : scp /Current/Path/File UserName@IP_Address:/Remote/Permissible/Path/

    RECIEVE COPIED FILE : scp UserName@IP_Address:/Remote/Permissible/Path/FileName


RSYNC : REMOTE SYNC

    SYNTAX : rsync -Options /Source/Path Destinatin_UserName@IP_Address:/Path/

        ARCHIVE FILES : -a OR --archive
        VERBOSE OUTPUT : -v OR --verbose
        COMPRESSION : -z OR --compress
        SHOW PROGRESS TRANSFER : --progress
        BACKUP BEFORE DELETE AT SOURCE : -b
        DELET BEFORE COPY AT SOURCE : -d
        PROVIDE BACKUP LOCATIO AT SOURCE : --backup-dir=/Path/

    SYNC DIRECTORY SUBDIRECTORIES FILES : rsync -r /Source/Path/Folder/* /Destination/Path

    SYNC DIRECTORY SUBDIRECTORIES FILES HIDDEN FILES : rsync -r /Source/Path/Folder/ /Destination/Path

    DELETE THINGS FROM DESTINATION NOT IN SOURCE : rsync -a /Source/Path/Folder/ /Destination/Path --delete

    SYNC ONLY UNCOMMON THINGS : 

        VIA CHECKSUMS : rsync -rc Source/Path/Folder/ /Destination/Path

        VIA TIMESTAMPS CHECK : rsync -a Source/Path/Folder/ /Destination/Path


        










